\begin_layout Standard
Rationalizing, we obtain
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
b_{n} & =n-\sqrt{n^{2}+2n}\cdot\frac{n+\sqrt{n^{2}+2n}}{n+\sqrt{n^{2}+2n}}\\
 & =\frac{n^{2}-n^{2}-2n}{n+\sqrt{n^{2}+2n}}=\frac{-2n}{n(1+\sqrt{1+\frac{2}{n}})}\\
 & =\frac{-2}{1+\sqrt{1+\frac{2}{n}}}.
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Since 
\begin_inset Formula $\lim(1/n)=0$
\end_inset

, the Algebraic Limit Theorem implies that 
\begin_inset Formula $\lim(2/n)=0$
\end_inset

 as well, and applying the ALT to the definition of 
\begin_inset Formula $b_{n}$
\end_inset

 yields
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\lim(b_{n})=\frac{-2}{1+\sqrt{1+0}}=\frac{-2}{2}=-1.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
